The Northern Trust Corporation is an American international financial services company headquartered in Chicago, Illinois. It provides investment management, asset and fund administration, and fiduciary and banking services through a network of 85 offices in 18 US states and 20 international offices in North America, Europe, and the Asia-Pacific. As of March 31 2017, Northern Trust Corporation had $121 billion in banking assets, $7.1 trillion in assets under custody and $1.0 trillion in assets under management. They are regulated by the Federal Reserve. In March 2010, Forbes magazine ranked Northern Trust as the world's most admired company in the "Superregional Banks" category.[4]
Other than M&T, Northern Trust was the only bank in the S&P 500 stock market index not to lower its dividend during the financial crisis of 2007–2008.[5]



